Be careful of over application OF CALCIUM NITRATE! ProCal and Advance cal are not calcium nitrates because, nitrate poisoning can occur as the result of eating crops such as Brassicas, green cereals or sweet clover that contain high levels of nitrate. However, the most common source is inorganic nitrate fertilizer, either directly, via grazing an over-fertilized field, or via water run-off from heavily fertilized fields. Spring is the most common season for nitrate poisoning.

Nitrate poisoning occurs because the nitrate is broken down to nitrite in the rumen. In normal circumstances this nitrite is further broken down to ammonia in the rumen and is then used by the rumen microbes to make protein. However, when large amounts of nitrate are eaten over a short period of time, the nitrite accumulates in the rumen and is absorbed. Once in the bloodstream it reacts with iron in the red blood cells so that they can no longer bind oxygen.

Be cautious of calcium nitrates, as they causes burning and poisoning that results in death to livestock. Bio-Active Liquid by AgriTec calcium WILL NOT burn and is safe for consumption by livestock. Nitrite Poisoning of Livestock Note Number: AG0701Published: February 2002 Updated: July 2008 

Nitrate accumulation in plants is a potential danger to grazing animals. It can cause two different disorders - nitrate poisoning and nitrite poisoning. Nitrates may cause inflammation of the gut when eaten in large quantities, but their main importance is as a source of nitrite. Nitrites cause respiratory distress due to interference with oxygenation of blood; death may follow. Pigs are the species most susceptible to nitrite poisoning, followed by cattle, sheep and horses.

Heading: Yellow Pine Flooring
Body:
Dreaming of affordable wood flooring? One of our most economical options is our Southern Yellow Pine tongue and groove flooring. We currently have a good inventory of 1x6. This is a common grade knotty yellow pine and will have a tremendous amount of beautiful character to it, as you can see in the pictures of the wood and our customers' homes. We can supply small projects and whole houses. 

Common Grade (#3) Southern Yellow Pine Flooring Pricing

The yellow pine is priced at $1.85 per sq ft for unopened packs and $1.95 if we have to split the packs. Again, pack sizes vary (as small as 400 sq ft to as large as 2,000 sq ft). These packs typically have one or two lengths in them. An unopened pack of 1,000 sq ft would cost $1,850 plus tax.

Linear foot price- $.76 per linear foot for 1x6 yellow pine flooring

We love to see your projects come to life and frequently share pictures of our customers' projects on Facebook. Check out our page (http://facebook.com/KentuckyLumber) for more pictures, our customers' ratings, and more information! 

Our inventory changes daily and we would highly encourage you to reserve wood before you come. We can't guarantee we will have anything in stock if you just drive to us.

Open Hours for appointments: 
Tuesday through Friday from 8-5 CST by appointment only
Saturday from 8-1 CST by appointment only
We are closed Sunday and Monday.

Kentucky Lumber LLC
Text/Call. Due to high volume, Text for a quicker and more efficient response.

Like us on Facebook: http://facebook.com/KentuckyLumber

We are located on Hwy 102 in Allensville, KY. Allensville is located 15 miles Southwest of Russellville, KY, 23 miles Northeast of Clarksville, TN, 21 miles North of Springfield, TN, and 48 miles Northwest of Nashville, TN.
